text: Its okay so far, but could you make a bit more elaborate pie chart, like include the feelings instead of others. Also, I have a suggestion, could you maybe add an option that explains feeling nothing. Like there are times when you feel nothing among the feelings that are given in the options. Some of the suggestions are kind of rude, so please work on that too. Overall I liked the app, but also include some tips instead of notifications. Thanks

This app is really helpful.  I rated it a four though for two reasons.  When I press on the stress emotion a little pop up comes up at the bottom asking if the things I'm stressed about are valid.  Yes they are.  Dont trivialize my emotions.  Second the smaller items are put into an other section on the pie chart.  It would be helpful to be able to view more details on those.

I think it is really a brilliant app with reagrd to its idea. However, it would be better to have more emotions, more than one emotional choice and an option not to check worried. Other than that great work! Thanks! I dont feel alone anymore, ur app cares for me. :)

Settings are very limited. It also inputs your info if you choose a feeling before you set your anxiety and you have to choose at least half a circle which I think is unfair as you may feel zero anxiety at the moment. Only been using this for two days but think it's cool just needs some improvements.

Designed to be simple and usable so that you really do make use of it a regular basis (it's most valuable when used regularly). Never seen anything like it before. Fantastic. Small criticisms: 1. Use of english is a bit off. He needs some proofreading done. 2. The graphs which show your emotional history are too limited. Especially the pie chart. Most of the time only 3 emotions are displayed on the pie chart. The other almost 50% represented simply as "other". Why not try a different type of chart, not pie? If these 2 things were fixed, I would pay to have adverts removed because I would know I would defo use it for a long time into the future.

Quite limited for now, you need more feelings to fulfill the app's purpose to it's maximum. "Other" feelings in report should be separate. I know it may be annoying to program but it would most likely get you better reviews. Please work on that

This app isn't at all what I expected. It won't allow you to multiselect , as if people only feel 1 emotion at a time. The range of emotion is also weak. There is more depth to human emotion than angry, anxious, happy etc. So, personally this is not helpful.
It helps me with keeping track of how my mood is throughout the day and night. I have severe mental illnesses. Too many to list but this is on app that i find very useful..

I was very disturbed to be given the suggestion of joining a religious cult rather than seek psychological counseling when I indicated that I was feeling very sad. This is extremely bad advice. The last thing  people need when they are feeling vulnerable is to be manipulated and exploited by religious mutters. An unethical app.
I think the app would improve a lot if it add the possibility of let a coment with the feeling. This way the user could see the reasons of his/her mood change.

I think this is an amazing and easy way to monitor emotions. The questionnaire is really easy and quick to complete, so it isn't a hassle on the go. It is a really  smart way to keep track, because honestly how many people can tell you every emotion they had over the course of 24 hours. A good idea, if the anxiety gauge was a bit more in depth, you could have an option for a reminder for when someone should take a dose o anxiety meds because sometimes it is hard to discern if you should or not when you are about to have a panic attack. :) just an idea though.

***This app only made my negative emotions WORSE*** ****TOO MANY POP UPS & ADS***** I tap an emotion to record how im feeling Im forced to multiple ads and forced to read repetitive pop up notifications on each emotion I tap to record.. Which then causes my phone to freeze and lag. I DONT NEED REPETITIVE INPUT, I NEED AWARENESS. Do you think its necessary to have vague pop ups every time i tap an emotion ?? This should be completely separate option. That's not effective awareness and or anger management. Seriously?! Amp up software development HUGE FAIL.
A nice idea, but perhaps people should be able to name their own emotions and put a fitting emoji with them. There should also be an option for 0 anxiety.

It could be so much more !There is very little directions and I'm not sure yet if it's worth the space on my phone. But I am going to keep the app for a small while until I determine whether it is worth it.
Its helpful but they could give it a better thought to the emotions considered. Could be either simplified to 4 or 5, or try to be more comprehensive including some missing emotions as 'feeling ok'
The app is really good overall but hey what if I don't feel any anxiety at a given moment. I can't submit data without selecting how much anxious I feel and I have to fill atleast half of it
Trying to monitor my mood swings and depression because of not being able to successfully communicate with my friends has been helping to determine when I am having ups and downs.
My chart is just 85% "other" and 15% thoghtful, which tells me nothing!! I want a better pie char and statistics

It's ok but, I think in order for me to give it a better rating it needs to have more different kinds of emotions (mood face symbols (or emoji) ) with the time of day mood recorded on to a chart for you on a journal page ( for you to add in an update, if you guys are able to do this for us), then cleared to record the following day, and so on.  Also, the monthly report should get recorded and evaluated, and then the user should get results back from a professional (or someone qualified) telling the user of your app, what their score is and give them percentages on different emotions for that month.  Then clear it out for the next month.  Is that too much to ask for?  I know it's a free app, but for me personally, if you did these changes, it would make your app alot better and I would stop my search for a better version.
I wish I didn't have to reset to 120 minutes every time.  It comes on every few minutes which causes stress in of itself.
replyText: You can configure to come every 300 minutes (5 hours) or then disable notification temporarily

text: I like the app so far, but I wish there was a button for "annoyed". I feel more annoyed than I do angry.
Well i think for the sake if being completely accurate i think there should be more emotions like honey or turned on and over whelmed, but rather than that  it's not that bad of an app.
There are way too less emotions that are listed. Human beings can experience lot more emotions at a time. There should be an option to select more than one emotion at the same time.
Iys ok, helps to detect your feelings but emoji arevery limited, like i couldn't find angry, upset, sleepy, fed up....

So stupid I wish I wasn't bored enough to even bother taking the time to write this except maybe it will save at least one person the time and energy it takes to install it, use it to answer the only 2 questions included in the app (yes, those screen shots really are the entire program), read the shockingly  useless information it contains, realize that's really all that it does or will ever do, and uninstall it.  I actually feel concerned for the person or people who created it...honestly, I hope this was meant to be a joke. If not, you've found a way to render valuable computer skills into utter uselesness and that's just sad. Seriously, rethink your life choices before it's too late.
More emotions and without the emoticons.  Or start with basic emotion and ask about more details.
I love this app. It helps me to calm down before making any stupid decisions.

It would be helpful to have a wider range of emotions; to be able to input your own labels of emotions would be even better.  Everyone has words they connect with that mean something specific to them that differs from the next person.
Am enjoying the app- I would have given it 5 stars except for the annoying wee messages when you enter an emotion- often they feel patronising and I have not found them helpful or applicable
